---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Home" description="Chris Gilbert - Senior Full Stack Engineer specializing in Ruby on Rails">
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Hi, I'm Chris Gilbert</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
      Senior Full Stack Engineer specializing in Ruby on Rails.
    </p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I like writing code I don't have to come back and explain to myself later, and I'd
        rather own a feature start to finish than hand it off halfway through. Currently at
        <a href="https://www.gosupercritical.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Supercritical</a>,
        helping businesses get to net zero through actual carbon removal (not offsets-and-a-prayer).
      </p>
      <p>
        Lately I've gone a bit deep on agentic AI tooling — Claude Code, custom skills, commands,
        the lot — trying to move faster without losing the taste that stops code turning into a
        mess six months later. I write up what's working (and what isn't) on the
        <a href="/blog">blog</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Based in London. Previously at Songkick and Multiverse. Former sound engineer
        turned software developer via Makers Academy.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-4 pt-4">
      <a
        href="/cv"
        class="inline-block bg-gray-900 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-gray-700 transition-colors"
      >
        View CV
      </a>
      <a
        href="/blog"
        class="inline-block border border-gray-300 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors"
      >
        Read Blog
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
